      "writtenOn": "2021-02-09T21:46:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why all the \u0027int\u0027 and not size_t?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 43,
        "startChar": 30,
        "endLine": 43,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "317480fce13dfbdb587b5954c8f6b21314b9a541",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a7484d0a_297cf384",
        "filename": "src/gpu/text/GrTextBlob.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 43,
      "author": {
        "id": 5210
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-02-09T22:57:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ve decided to use int through the entire system. One of the big reasons is that UBSan can catch overflows of signed things. I have found it harder to make overflow mistakes using int.",
      "parentUuid": "d9bf52f7_3a472b02",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 43,
        "startChar": 30,
        "endLine": 43,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "317480fce13dfbdb587b5954c8f6b21314b9a541",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c5496fcb_bd31459c",
        "filename": "src/gpu/text/GrTextBlob.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 43,
      "author": {
        "id": 5140
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-02-10T16:33:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I suppose, but could it be something at least a bit more suggestive like ptrdiff_t (which is essentially signed size_t)? \u0027int\u0027 is such an arbitrary and often wrong sized integer type for the size of a memory allocation. In fact, I would prefer the API take size_t and then do all the release asserts when narrowing to ptrdiff_t internally. This is essentially what Android does as well (any malloc larger than the positive range of ptrdiff_t will just crash, not even return NULL like if it was just a big unsatisfiable request).",
      "parentUuid": "a7484d0a_297cf384",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 43,
        "startChar": 30,
        "endLine": 43,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "317480fce13dfbdb587b5954c8f6b21314b9a541",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
